Asterisk Call Routing Stability & SIP Contact Management
Project focused on resolving call routing inconsistencies in an Asterisk PBX environment using standard SIP practices.

Investigated inbound call delivery issues and routing instability
Identified multiple SIP contacts as the root cause of non-deterministic behavior
Applied single-contact enforcement in PJSIP configuration
Validated call delivery using CLI originate and channel state verification
Confirmed correct inbound and outbound call handling
Developed a health check script for automated validation
Implemented backup and recovery procedures to prevent configuration drift

Result: Stable, predictable, and validated call routing behavior.
